{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Work to establish a global Severance Guarantee Fund for those in clothing supply",
        "additional_details": "Most people making clothes for UK brands are employed in low-wage countries without social protection systems.\r\n\r\nAs UK brands go insolvent, factories - and their workers - are low on the list of creditors resulting in unpaid orders, unemployment, and unpaid wages and severance.\r\n\r\nGarment workers in vulnerable supply chains should not pay the price when UK brands go insolvent. The government must also tell UK brands to #PayYourWorkers.\r\n\r\nFor more info: https://labourbehindthelabel.org/campaigns/covid-19-impact/\r\n",
        "background": "The government must work with other governments around the world to establish a global Severance Guarantee Fund to provide legally mandated severance pay and outstanding wages to garment workers in global supply chains when factories, or UK brands like Topshop or Debenhams, enter administration.",
